videos.headline: Webb's perfect throw puts Cal ahead with 29-yard TD strike
videos.description: Davis Webb backpedals in the face of the on-rushing defense before firing a strike to Jordan Veasy in the corner of the end zone to give Cal the early 7-0 lead on Texas.

videos.headline: Cal drops ball at the 1-yard line; ends game in controversy
videos.description: On 3rd-and-1, Cal RB Vic Enwere takes off for the end zone but drops the ball at the 1-yard line. Initially called a touchdown, it's overturned giving the Golden Bears the ball as there was no immediate recovery. The Bears hold on to upset Texas 50-43.

tracking.trackingName: NCF_One-Play (Cal drops ball at the 1-yard line; ends game in controversy) 2016/9/17 ESHEET

videos.headline: Cal upsets Texas, not without controversy
videos.description: QB Davis Webb records 396 yards and four touchdowns in the Bears' victory, but RB Vic Enwere's dropped ball at the 1-yard line created a controversial end to California's 50-43 win over No. 11 Texas.
